cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with natural language processing and deep encoders to generate representations of text content, which falls under the purview of cs.CL.
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with predicting the quality of edits in Wikipedia, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval task.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper utilizes deep learning models for predicting edit quality, which falls under the purview of cs.LG.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with developing automated tools for content moderation and review, which can be seen as a form of AI.
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper deals with content moderation and review in Wikipedia, which has implications for the societal impact of technology.
